  "source": "[\\set]\nDescribes: X\nsatisfies:\n. forAll: Y is \\set\n  then: \\axiom.of.extension#given{A := X; B := Y}\n. \\axiom.of.specification#given{X}\n. \\axiom.of.empty.set\nEnables:\n. capability: x_ \"in\" X :-> \\\\abstract\nDocumented:\n. called: \"set\"\n. description: \"The primitive object of the theory. Belonging is the undefined notion: for a set $x$ and a set $A$, either $x \\in A$ or $x \\notin A$.\"\nId: \"27f9dbd5-5b5e-4be3-b280-1afef8411f2d\"",
